<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-44-0367 </DOCNO><TEXT>The state and development prospects of nuclear power engineering in Czechoslovakiaare considered. At present six nuclear power units of total installedpower capacity 2640 MW with WWER-440 type reactors operate in the country.The construction of the Temelin four-unit NPP with WWER-1000 type reactorsis started. Great attention is paid to emergency planning. Certain dataon radiation monitoring after the accident at the Chernobyl NPP are presented.</TEXT></DOC>